    "summary": "Agility CMS exposes 4 developer HTTP APIs (Content Fetch, GraphQL, Content Sync, and Management), 2 MCP servers (one OAuth-protected CMS server and one public docs server), and an npm CLI; auth uses instance API keys for fetch/sync/GraphQL, OAuth for CLI/CMS MCP, and PATs are documented for Management API but on-wire mechanics were not confirmed from public docs.",
    "credentials": {
      "fetch_api_key": {
        "type": "api_key",
        "label": "Content Fetch/Preview API key",
        "generateUrl": "https://agilitycms.com/docs/developers/content-fetch-api",
        "setup": "In Agility CMS, go to [Settings > API Keys](https://agilitycms.com/docs/developers/content-fetch-api). Create an API key, choose its type (`fetch` for published content or `preview` for staging content), and copy the secret. The same page shows your instance GUID and regional API host."
      },
      "agility_oauth_user": {
        "type": "oauth2",
        "label": "Agility user OAuth login",
        "generateUrl": "https://agilitycms.com/docs/developers/cli",
        "setup": "Use the easiest supported login path for developer tools: run `agility login` for the CLI or connect from an MCP client to the Agility CMS MCP server, which uses OAuth 2.0. For PAT creation, the docs state PATs can only be created by users authenticated via OAuth; manage them via the Management API Swagger at [mgmt.aglty.io](https://mgmt.aglty.io/index.html)."
      },
      "pat": {
        "type": "bearer",
        "label": "Personal Access Token",
        "generateUrl": "https://mgmt.aglty.io/index.html",
        "setup": "First authenticate as an Agility user via OAuth; the docs say PATs can only be created by users authenticated via OAuth. Then create and manage the token through the Management API's “Personal Access Tokens” section in [Management API Swagger](https://mgmt.aglty.io/index.html), as described in [Personal Access Tokens - Public Beta](https://agilitycms.com/docs/developers/personal-access-tokens-public-beta). Copy the token secret when shown — it is displayed only once."
      }
    },
